{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17509259","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17509259"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:15:31+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:15:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11408"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11408","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11408"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.3,0.06,0.07,0.06,0.51]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4044"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110550"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4044","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4044"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11408"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92807"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"106"},{"type":"tags","id":"1036"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"2602"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"9735"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"4642"},{"type":"contributions","id":"5197"},{"type":"contributions","id":"5992"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19205"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41755"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110550","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/110550"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 53-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a one-month history of intermittent palpitations and fatigue. He has a medical history of asthma and bipolar disorder. His medications include salbutamol inhaler as needed and lithium. He does not smoke and drinks alcohol socially. He works as an accountant and has not travelled recently.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well. His pulse rate is 120/min and irregularly irregular, blood pressure 126/84 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 36.8\u00b0C. Cardiovascular examination reveals an irregularly irregular rhythm with no murmurs. The remainder of the examination is unremarkable.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInvestigations reveal an ECG showing atrial fibrillation with a ventricular rate of 120/min (Image). An echocardiogram is unremarkable with normal left ventricular function and no structural abnormalities.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following pharmacologic treatments would be most appropriate regarding anticoagulation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["No specific treatment required","Aspirin","Aspirin and clopidogrel","Warfarin","Apixaban"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis is an individual who has presented with newly diagnosed atrial fibrillation that is likely paroxysmal in nature. In addition to immediate rate control, an important aspect in the treatment of atrial fibrillation is long-term anticoagulation in order to prevent thromboembolic complications such as stroke.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn order to determine an individual\u0027s thromboembolic risk in atrial fibrillation, it is important to calculate their CHA2DS2-VA score.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECHA2DS2-VA score:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECongestive heart failure:\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cem\u003E1 point\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypertension:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cem\u003E 1 point\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAge \u226575:\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cem\u003E2 points\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiabetes mellitus:\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cem\u003E1 point\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrevious stroke:\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cem\u003E2 points\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVascular disease: \u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cem\u003E1 point\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAge 65-74:\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cem\u003E1 point\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAs this individual has a CHA2DS2-VA score of 0, \u003Cstrong\u003Eno specific form of anticoagulation\u003C/strong\u003E is required. Individuals with a CHA2DS2-VA score of \u003E2 will require long-term anticoagulation, with direct oral anticoagulants (DOAC\u0027s) recommended as first line.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWarfarin\u003C/strong\u003E would be a suitable alternative however it requires regular INR monitoring whereas DOAC\u0027s can be given as a fixed dose with a rapid onset of action.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst \u003Cstrong\u003Easpirin\u003C/strong\u003E has historically been an option for individuals with CHA2DS2-VA score of 1, current evidence does not show any benefit in the use of aspirin monotherapy as a means of thromboembolic prophylaxis in atrial fibrillation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAspirin and clopidogrel\u003C/strong\u003E dual antiplatelet therapy is not indicated for stroke prevention in atrial fibrillation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EApixaban\u003C/strong\u003E is a direct oral anticoagulant that would be appropriate for patients with a CHA2DS2-VA score of 2 or greater, but is not indicated in this patient with a score of 0.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn the case of cardioversion, anticoagulation is recommended. In this scenario the heart rate is too slow to consider cardioversion, so this is not a consideration.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["No anticoagulation is required for a CHA2DS2-VA score of zero."],"references":["Briffa T, Maiorana A, Chew DP, et al. National Heart Foundation of Australia. Clinical exercise recommendations for individuals with cardiovascular disease: Guidance for healthcare professionals. Heart Lung Circ 2018;27(10):1192\u20131206. Available at: https://www.heartlungcirc.org/article/S1443-9506(18)31778-5/fulltext","Gao X, Passman R. Stroke Prevention in Atrial Fibrillation. Curr Cardiol Rep 2022;24:1765-74."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92807"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11408"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"15719"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"15719","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15719"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/0fc1004e-2bca-453c-8bf0-3bc2de213c42.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/0fc1004e-2bca-453c-8bf0-3bc2de213c42.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":800,"height":411}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92807","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/92807"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-08-01T11:28:13+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-01T11:28:29+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4044"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110550"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":